{
 "name": "RPlog_Unusual_Courtesy",
 "title": "Unusual Courtesy: A Captured Blockade Runner",
 "summary": "After a New Republic blockade runner is disabled and snared in the Broadsword's hangar, the Imperial pilot Krieg (Lieutenant Inrokana) boards it alone to find its sole occupant, the young trader Shael Winters, who had kept firing to cover the escape of her X-wing escorts. Rather than brutalize her as she fears, Krieg treats her with surprising civility, escorting her to a break room while Captain Caiton oversees stormtroopers stripping the freighter Camerata bare of cargo, weapons, and components. Over a guarded conversation, Shael spins a cover story about being a simple trader hauling relief supplies for Coruscant's starving while Krieg, unconvinced but uninterested in harming her, confiscates her credits and forged ID per intelligence's orders and outfits her in a pressure suit. True to his word, he returns the gutted, one-way-equipped ship to her and lets her go, and the two part with an unexpected handshake before Caiton's crew finish the confiscation and hurl the stripped freighter and debris on a tractor-beam toss toward Coruscant.",
